Playboy’s $185 Million LBO Loan Rises in First Trade

-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 
2011-02-28T22:15:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/playboy-s-185-million-lbo-loan-rises-in-first-trade-correct-.html
(Corrects loan amount in first paragraph.)    Playboy Enterprises Inc .’s $185
million term loan to finance the company’s buyout by founder
Hugh M. Hefner rose in its first trade, according to information
provider Markit Group Ltd.  The six-year debt, issued at par, was first bid at 99.5
cents on the dollar and then changed hands at 100.5 cents,
Markit said.  Jefferies Group Inc. arranged the Chicago-based company’s
loan with an interest rate 6.5 percentage points more than the
London interbank offered rate and a 1.75 percent floor on the
lending benchmark, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in New York at 
